  "text": "• C for 4 hours. The glucosinolate content and fiber characteristics in RSM, dehulled RSM, and defatted rapeseed hulls were determined by HPLC (ISO 9167-1:1992) . The crude fiber (CF) content was measured using the Weende method (NF V03-040). Neutral detergent fiber (NDF), acid detergent fiber (ADF), and acid detergent lignin (ADL) were obtained according to [CITATION_1] . Phytase activity was measured according to [CITATION_2] . Distal ileum content was freeze-dried. Samples were then ashed at 550",
